

Describes the semantics of concurrent programs. Was re-defined by JSR 133 (part of Java 5). Allows operations in threads to be re-ordered, as long as certain partial ordering, *happens-before//, is followed; this ensures that the operations will appear to all threads as if they were performed serially in the order provided by the programmer.

